# docs/

Durable, human-facing documentation, organized by [Diátaxis](https://diataxis.fr).
Per-feature specs/plans/tasks are spec-kit artifacts and live in `specs/`, not here.
Project principles live in `.specify/memory/constitution.md`.

| Folder | Diátaxis mode | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| [`tutorials/`](tutorials/README.md) | Learning | Step-by-step lessons for newcomers. |
| [`how-to/`](how-to/README.md) | Task | Goal-oriented recipes and runbooks. |
| [`reference/`](reference/README.md) | Information | Vocabulary, schemas, APIs, config — looked up, not read through. |
| [`explanation/`](explanation/README.md) | Understanding | Rationale, background, trade-offs. |
| [`decisions/adrs/`](decisions/adrs/README.md) | — | MADR architecture decisions (`NNNN-slug.md`, never renumbered). |
| `history/` | — | Dated point-in-time notes kept for context only. |

## When to write where

Pick the Diátaxis mode by **the reader's need**: learning → `tutorials/`; doing a
task → `how-to/`; looking something up → `reference/`; understanding why →
`explanation/`. A decision worth preserving → `decisions/adrs/`.
